- ##%%A and B can do a job together in 7 days. A is 1\(\frac{3}{4}\) times as efficient as B. The 4 same job can be done by A alone in how many days?%%## {link:https://youtu.be/MvOfmFR-s78?t=943}@@Link@@{/}
=> \(x:y\) = \(1:1\)\(\frac{3}{4}\)
=> \(X:Y\) = \(4:7\)
=> \(\frac{X}{Y}\) = \(\frac{4}{7}\)
=> \(\frac{1}{Y}\) = \(\frac{4}{7x}\)
=> \(\frac{1}{x}\) + \(\frac{1}{y}\) = \(\frac{1}{7}\)

